org.cds06.speleograph.data

Class SpeleoDataFileReader.HeaderInformation

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cds06.speleograph.data.SpeleoDataFileReader.HeaderInformation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Enclosing class:
    SpeleoDataFileReader

    public static class SpeleoDataFileReader.HeaderInformation
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Information about a file header.

    A file header is a pack of information which are which series we will read, which columns are liked to a series, what are the date columns, how to parse the date ...

    This class is designed to be used by two classes, the first is ImportTable which will populate this class with user information, the second is SpeleoDataFileReader which will use it to parse the file fast.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Philippe VIENNE
    See Also:
    This class is serializable to be saved in case we have to reuse it., Serialized Form

    • Field Detail

      • numberOfSeriesToParse

        protected int numberOfSeriesToParse
        Number of read Series. This value is computed to go faster while iterating series or columns. It must be a computed value and never be visible for elements outside this class.

      • series

        protected Series[] series
        Series array, it contains all series to read mapped to an id (the index).

      • columns

        protected Integer[][] columns
        Columns array, contains the columns id to read for a Series.

        Each entry in this array is designed as the following rules :

        • [int]: is a single column data and series admit only a value per item
        • [int, int]: each item has a minimal value (first index) and maximal value(second index)
        • [int, int, int]: 0 is a value, 1 a minimal value and 2 a maximal value
        each entry in this array which has null length or length gather than 3 will be ignored.

      • firstLineOfData

        protected int firstLineOfData
        The line in the file where we will start to read data.

      • dateInformation

        protected SpeleoDataFileReader.DateInformation dateInformation
        Information about date columns.

        A column used for a Date element should not be used for a data.

        Set data information for a Series and Columns.
        Parameters:
        series - The series to add (should be not null)
        column - The column information with this format:
        • [int]: is a single column data and series admit only a value per item
        • [int, int]: each item has a minimal value (first index) and maximal value(second index)
        • [int, int, int]: 0 is a value, 1 a minimal value and 2 a maximal value
        Returns:
        0 if it creates a new entry, 1 if it update one, -1 in case of error.
